Continuing Dr. King’s work is the best way we can honor his legacy, and bring his dream to life.
We need to preserve programs to protect the poor, level the economic playing field, and protect access to quality education and healthcare.
We’ve come a long way from the hate that Dr. King gave his life trying to fight. But that doesn’t mean that we’ve solved all our problems.
even to provide access to contraception so that families can make the choices that work for them.
to create a fair tax code and financial regulations that do more than just prop up the highest earners...
We’re still fighting to build a world-class education system for all students in every community...
The battles he fought still continue today—even some of the lesser heralded issues.
King’s message wasn't just racial equality – it was equal economic opportunity and equal chances to succeed for every American.
